longBusinessSummary: Emgold Mining Corporation, a gold and base metals exploration company, acquires, explores for, and develops mineral properties in Canada and the United States. It explores for gold, silver, molybdenum, copper, and other mineral deposits. The company's flagship property is the Golden Arrow consisting of 17 patented claims and 494 unpatented claims covering an area of approximately 10,000 acres located to the east of Tonopah, Nevada, the United States. It also holds 100% interests in the New York Canyon, Mindora, Buckskin Rawhide East, Buckskin Rawhide West, and Koegel Rawhide properties located Nevada, the United States; and the Casa South and the East-West properties located in Quebec, Canada. The company was formerly known as Emperor Gold Corporation and changed its name to Emgold Mining Corporation in August 1997. Emgold Mining Corporation was incorporated in 1989 and is based in Vancouver, Canada.
